From f38e383c64ad9585a67e731654b67052e4213516 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Audit Orchestrator <audit@vocaboost.local>
Date: Sun, 31 May 2026 07:13:54 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Fix B27-F01: exclude MASTERED words from review queue

buildReviewQueue mapped all segment words (including MASTERED) into the
pool for selectReviewQueue, which has no MASTERED priority branch. Once a
segment's eligible (non-mastered) pool shrank below reviewCount, mastered
words leaked into the review test and got re-tested - downgrading earned
mastery (MASTERED->PASSED). Confirmed in the B27 canary (careful/TOP day 16:
27/27 review words were MASTERED with future returnAt).

Filter out status===MASTERED before selection. Expired MASTERED words are
already flipped to NEEDS_CHECK by returnMasteredWords() at session init, so
anything still MASTERED here is within its 21-day rest window.

Known adjacent gap (NOT fixed here): selectReviewQueue also has no
NEEDS_CHECK branch - flagged for follow-up.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
